videoDetails.title: PBS News Weekend full episode, July 9, 2023
videoDetails.shortDescription:
Sunday on PBS News Weekend, how some Americans are paying each other’s medical bills through health care sharing plans, an unregulated alternative to traditional insurance. Then, the challenges the U.S. military faces as it adopts artificial intelligence on the battlefield. Plus, a conversation with the author of “American Born Chinese” on turning his acclaimed graphic novel into a TV series.

WATCH TODAY’S SEGMENTS:
News Wrap: NATO to discuss Ukraine’s bid to join alliance
https://youtu.be/_eVPZJavzTk 
Why many Americans use unregulated health care sharing plans
https://youtu.be/Crp5H5oJ52A 
How militaries are using AI on and off the battlefield
https://youtu.be/Fdgh1JuKeXI
Gene Luen Yang on bringing ‘American Born Chinese’ to TV
https://youtu.be/gWmrX8glhTk
